==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Drawbridge
<hw>Draw"bridge`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A bridge of which
either the whole or a part is made to be raised up, let down, or drawn
or turned aside, to admit or hinder communication at pleasure, as before
the gate of a town or castle, or over a navigable river or
canal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The movable portion, or draw, is called, specifically, a
<xex>bascule</xex>, <xex>balance</xex>, or <xex>lifting bridge</xex>, a
<xex>turning</xex>, <xex>swivel</xex>, or <xex>swing bridge</xex>, or a
<xex>rolling bridge</xex>, according as it turns on a hinge vertically,
or on a pivot horizontally, or is pushed on rollers.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Drawcansir</ent>⟦br⟧
